# Penta Application Screener Rules

This file is the shared working agreement for Codex, Cline, and any other agent working on this repo.

## Project Intent

- Build an application screener for Penta Housing Coop applications.
- Source application data from Google Drive spreadsheets in the Penta Drive folder.
- Support deterministic hard filters before any AI-assisted review.
- Use AI primarily for interpreting essay-question answers and helping narrow qualified candidates.
- Produce committee-ready reports for MOMI (Move In Move Out) with recommendations and justifications.

## Collaboration

- Keep the product specification current as decisions are made.
- Treat `SPEC.md` as the product source of truth; update it when behavior, architecture, or milestone scope changes.
- Prefer asking clarifying questions before implementing unclear product behavior.
- When asking product or architecture questions, briefly explain meaningful tradeoffs where appropriate so Jeff can make informed decisions.
- Treat applicant data as sensitive personal information.
- Do not expose secrets, raw private application data, or unnecessary personal details in logs, commits, or reports.
- Keep implementation choices documented enough that work can move between Codex and Cline without losing context.
- Jeff handles commits at stable milestones unless he explicitly asks an agent to commit.

## Engineering Defaults

- Start simple and testable.
- Follow the implementation defaults in `SPEC.md`: `uv`, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy/Alembic, pytest, Vite React, npm, SQLite, and cookie-based sessions unless Jeff changes the plan.
- Separate deterministic screening logic from AI-assisted evaluation logic.
- Make AI decisions auditable: preserve prompts, model outputs, score rationales, and user choices where appropriate.
- Design for human override at every candidate-screening stage.
- Avoid irreversible writes to source Google Drive data unless the user explicitly approves them.
- Do not commit `.env` files, OAuth secrets, SQLite database files, applicant exports, AI traces, or raw prompts/model outputs containing applicant data.
